You will see it if you set a counter at the text of one of the `Button`s. The counter increases endlessly.&lt;br/&gt;
The setting of `Button`s&#39; new layout size in the `Handler` is followed by a new call of the `OnLayoutChangeListener` and this `Listener` starts the `Handler` again and so on &lt;br/&gt;
You will get the same problem if you are using the `OnGlobalLayoutListener` instead of the `OnLayoutChangeListener` with a `Handler`.&lt;br/&gt;
The reason is the following. The `view.requestLayout()` or `view.setLayoutParams()` does not work in the `onLayoutChange` method, but it works in the `onGlobalLayout` method or in a `Handler` which creates a new thread.&lt;br/&gt;
