A successful call on the `child.requestLayout()` makes a new call on the parent&#39;s `onLayoutChange` method. This is peculiar because the parent&#39;s layout should not change again.&lt;br/&gt;
However that be, a little if/else logic solves the endless calls.

&lt;!-- language: java --&gt;

